<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 8:00AM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHERN SOMERSET COUNTY THROUGH
830 AM EDT...
At 759 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Somerset, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Somerset, Meyersdale, Berlin, Ursina, New Centerville, Rockwood,
Garrett, Indian Lake, Shanksville, Casselman, Callimont and Seven
Springs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
